# Interpreter for: stop [interface] (TERMINAL FUNCTION)
# Resolves to _stop0 (no args) or _stop1 (with interface) via right-to-left resolution
#
# Function role: Terminal function - generates session cleanup commands
# Output: Shell commands to stop VPN sessions (calls protocol-specific disconnect functions)
#
# This interpreter executes the stop commands which iterate through active sessions
# and call the appropriate disconnect function for each protocol.
#
# Override for dry-run:
#   echo "cat" > .env/local/VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_stop
